# 🚨 Day 23: Incident Detection & Response Fundamentals

## 📘 Topics Covered:
- Definition of **Security Incidents**
- Event vs Incident: Real-world examples
- **Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)** & **Indicators of Attack (IOAs)**
- Incident Response Lifecycle (NIST SP 800-61)
- Preparation
- Detection & Analysis
- Containment, Eradication & Recovery
- Post-Incident Activities
- Common response tools: SIEM, EDR, Zeek, Suricata

## 🛠️ Commands Practiced:

### 🔍 Detection:

netstat -anob   - Windows: View network connections with process info
ss -tulnp       -      # Linux: Check listening ports and services
tasklist        -       # Windows: List running processes
ps aux          -       # Linux: View running processes
ipconfig /displaydns -  # Windows: View cached DNS
tcpdump -i any port 53  -   # Linux: Monitor DNS traffic
